      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACKPOOL FINN (7) looks close to another win after finishing second from Box 1 last time (22.35) at Warrnambool. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Capable of going well again. SPECIAL LAD (1) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot before finishing second (22.13) and beaten 1.5 lengths over 390m at Ballarat. Has a solid record from this box including four wins and a minor placing. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. RAM RAID (2) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at Warrnambool over 390m behind Blessed Rain (22.81) in a Free For All. Was a winner prior to that. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MR. CHIVES (3) placed last time (22.84) at Warragul in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 3 lengths. Already a winner from this draw.",
